text.text: Today, I had my first ever arancini here (one of the several different vegetarian/vegan ones on offer). It turned out to be absolutely delicious! Had another one the same evening! Francesco is very enthusiastic and passionate about the food served and provides a great service! Makes eating here, a wonderful experience!

text.text:
We are on holiday in lido di jesolo.
The first time we went there we were going to verona but our first stop was padova to walk around and see the city. My dad is half sicilian and we saw Sicilian Goodness. And i really wanted to taste the arancini.
So we just bought 2 arancinis. We didnt know what to expect but it was really delicious. It was so delicious that we decided to visit padova the last time on our last day just to go back there.

This time we asked for canolli. She told us to come back tomorrow because they dont have anymore. But we said we are not there tomorrow anymore. We are going back home.
So she told us to wait and she made us 4 diffrent canolli specially for us. I told her about my sicilian roots and they recommended us a granita. She let us taste diffrent kinds of granitas so we could choose the flavour we liked.
It tasted really amazing. Also the ice was really good.
Of course we also had arancinis and bought also for our way back home.

The shop owner and the workers were the most friendliest people we met in italy. Pretty good english and such awesome service.
We told them that we will definitely come back. Our next vacation will be in austria but then we make a trip to padova JUST to come back!

Food is awesome
Service is awesome
And everyone who works there is really kind and sweet.

We wish you all the best.
Keep up the amazing work you do.
Until we meet again, next year!!

Greetings from the Netherlands from
Fabrizio and Samantha

text.text:
This Sicilian food store/bar has fabulous arancini so similar to the original that will make you question whether they are actually vegan! 😂🌱

Portions are generous and if you go towards the closing there is a "get 4 pay 10€" promotion: therefore 2.50€ each!

They also have some vegan authentic granitas: I’ll come back to try them ☀️💐

text.text:
Not to bad. Though my husband is venetian, he loves sicilia. He goes often for work in the south. But any time we see a place selling the food we have to stop.
Over all the place isn't bad. The girls working here are great except the short girl with dirty blonde hair. She has a major attitude problem with co workers and customers. Maybe she's related to the owner. Or she's there to give Authentic southern charm? I've only been as far south to brindisi. So I can't say anything. Only many tell me people from Naples, Rome and Taranto can have this attitude. Ok. To each their own. I loved Rome. 😍 hope to see Naples when not busy.

Other than that this is a good place.
I do prefer the northern Italian style food though.

text.text: Sicilian hospitality and excellent local specialties served by friendly girls, thank you. We couldn't decide what to try first, we decided on Arancini and Cannoli, they are excellent, you must try them. You can't miss this place if you want real Italian specialties to take away😊
